        <abstract>
            <p>Sends advice on naturalist matters.</p> 
<p>W. H. Harvey’s work [with Wilhelm Sonder, <hi rend="italic">Flora capensis</hi> (1859–65)],</p>  
<p>and Robert Brown’s publication ["On the organs and mode of fecundation in Orchideae and Asclepiadeae", <hi rend="italic">Trans. Linn. Soc. Lond.</hi> 16 (1833): 685–745].</p>  
<p>Writes of having seen in S. America a Hymenopteran with tarsi covered with pollen-masses of <hi rend="italic">Asclepias</hi>.</p> 
            <p>Interested in JPMW’s researches in South American caverns.</p>
            <p>Mentions poor health.</p>
            <p>Thanks for tracings.</p>
        </abstract>
